  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance "Randy Hanson, a resident of Wisconsin, was visiting his family in Barstow Ca. On September 09, 2022, Hanson left his family's residence in his black 2007 BMW sedan with one of his local acquaintances. He was supposed to return later in the evening and then drive back to WI the next day. He never returned home, and family has not heard from him since that day. His car was later found abandoned in the desert. The clothing he left the house wearing was folded on the back seat of the car. His cell phone and a broken GPS device were found in the vehicle. Foul play is suspected."^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/120420?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/120420/Images/203507/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

