  rdfs:hasMapData </ser531/ontologies/MissingPersonReport#http%3A//www.google.com/maps/place/35.7283017%2C-120.879626>;
  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance """On 3-6-22, the Sheriff's Office received a report from a family member of an at-risk missing person out of Heritage Ranch.
The family member last made contact with Endes on 3-4-22. At that time, it's believed Endes was having a mental health crisis. When Deputies responded to his residence in Heritage Ranch, Endes was not at the location, but his vehicle was still in the driveway, and he had left his personal and work phones at the residence. Neighbors reported that Endes had asked them if they could look after his dog for a couple days while he went on a walkabout. Endes was last seen by his neighbors near his backyard in a creek bed. Endes wearing all black clothing with a black jacket and black beanie."""^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/94650?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/94650/Images/177887/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

