  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance "Antonio Hernandez was last seen on a bicycle at 17th St and Harbor Blvd in Santa Ana, CA by his wife on 5/09/19 at 1830 hours. He believed someone was following him so he went to \"go hide.\" He was not seen after that date and reported missing to Tustin Police Department 9 days later. The report was sent to Anaheim PD because Hernandez was an Anaheim resident. It was not known if Antonio Hernandez had any mental disorder. He was last known to be living homeless and would solicit for contractor work at the Home Depot in Westminster, CA."^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/97338?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/97338/Images/181311/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

