  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance """Cabada was involved in a dispute with his girlfriend and she left the home. She left the area for a week and has not seen or heard from Cabada since 07/17-2011. On 07/26/2011 his girlfriend located the vehicle which they shared parked and locked at a local but rural park, in Ukiah. None of Cabada's family in the Ukiah area or in Mexico have heard from him since the July 2011. Cabada also uses the names: Rosario Lopez and Rosario Lopez Bobadilla.

Cabada has a history of being a field worker. He usually dresses in long sleeved shirts and size 9 dress shoes."""^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/30514?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/30514/Images/39619/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

