  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance "Francisco told his family in January 2009 that he would be going home (México) in February 2009. The family has not heard from him since then. An uncle has claimed that he saw Francisco in Santa Ana, and that he was in bad shape (drinking). The family doesn’t believe it The family says that Francisco did not drink or smoke—he has always been a responsible father and husband. As far as the family understands, he was living alone in Santa Ana. He worked as a sawmill operator, cutting trees. (I’m not sure where—the family says they saw a video he made of his work, cutting trees and throwing the branches in a truck. Possibly a landscaper?)."^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/21822?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/21822/Images/11088/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

