  mpr:hasCircumstanceOfDisappearance "Ivy, Violet, and Yolanda are sisters. During the early morning hours of July 20, 1977, law enforcement officials responded to a fire at the children's home. The children's mother was found deceased inside the home and the children were discovered missing. In addition, a male child by the name of Sir-Kristopher Marshall, who had spent the night at the children's home, was also discovered missing. His photo may be viewed at www.missingkids.com. Ivy and Violet are listed in NamUs as 6365 and 6364. Sir-Kristopher is listed in NamUs as 6344."^^xsd:String;
  mpr:columnURI "https://www.namus.gov/MissingPersons/Case#/6807?nav"^^xsd:String;
  mpr:hasImageURL "https://www.namus.gov/api/CaseSets/NamUs/MissingPersons/Cases/6807/Images/61512/Thumbnail"^^xsd:String .

